The factors ensure that system testing is thorough, and the application meets the required standards. 
By confirming these factors, you can ensure that testing is complete, and the system is ready for release or deployment.
Factors:
1. Test Case Execution: All planned test cases have been executed, and results are documented.
2. Defect Closure: All critical and high-priority defects have been resolved or mitigated.
3. Test Coverage: All requirements have been tested, and coverage is adequate.
4. Stakeholder Approval: Stakeholders have approved the test results and summary report.
5. Test Exit Criteria: All test exit criteria have been met, as defined in the test plan.
6. No Critical Issues: No critical or blocking issues remain unresolved.
7. Test Environment: Test environment is restored to its original state.
